# Admin UI — HeroUI only

The admin app (`frontend/apps/admin`) uses **@heroui/react v3**. All interactive controls must come from HeroUI, not native HTML.

## Form controls

| Need | Use | Never use |
|------|-----|-----------|
| Text | `FormTextField` | `<input>`, raw `TextField` without wrapper |
| Select | `FormSelectField` | `<select>`, native dropdown |
| Date (single) | `FormDatePicker` | `<input type="date">`, `FormTextField` with `type="date"` |
| Date range (from/to) | `FormDateRangePicker` | Two separate `FormDatePicker` fields |
| Number | `FormNumberField` or `NumberField` | `<input type="number">` |
| Toggle | `Switch` from HeroUI | `<input type="checkbox">` |
| Buttons | `Button` from HeroUI | `<button>` with custom classes |

## Date picker composition

- Single date: `FormDatePicker` (`@/components/ui/FormDatePicker.tsx`)
- **From/to pairs**: `FormDateRangePicker` (`@/components/ui/FormDateRangePicker.tsx`) — always use for validity periods; never two separate pickers
- Both use `DatePicker`/`DateRangePicker` + `DateField` + `Calendar`/`RangeCalendar` from `@heroui/react`
- Value/onChange: ISO date strings `YYYY-MM-DD` (via `@/lib/date-values`)
- Range validation: `isIsoDateRangeInvalid`; block save when end < start

## Before adding a new field

1. Check `@/components/ui/FormFields.tsx` and `@/components/ui/FormDatePicker.tsx`
2. Extend an existing wrapper if the pattern repeats
3. Match `variant="secondary"` and `fullWidth` like other form fields
